OneHouse is an innovative and user-focused real estate marketplace in Hong Kong, and expanding to Asia cities, provided by EC Property (HK) Limited.

With its epoch-making user experience, owners, buyers, tenants and real estate agents would have a totally new and unimaginable way to find your home, as reflected in its slogan - Experience Your Way Home ().

Differentiated from other property websites which are swamped with fake or unavailable listings and information initiated by real estate agents in order to lure customers, OneHouse offers a comprehensive two-pronged approach, combining online and offline solutions to effectively solve the problem and ensure the authenticity of information.

Driving to equip consumers with easy and handy tools in the process of property transaction to realise real estate agent professionalisation and individualisation, we help them to build up their profile, portfolios and track records with first class marketing tools and latest software to manage and enhance their business.

We are the member company of the Incu-App Programme of Hong Kong Science Park and have offices both in Science Park and Causeway Bay. We are currently building a diligent, creative and energetic team of designers and developers to be part of our company.

What a surprise to find a whole thread and blog post dedicated to the search for my identity.

I consent to a benevolent search for my identity or identities. I was quite surprised to see the speed and scale of this development - another symptom of networked life.

Some of the speculation is very interesting. It's also surprising what accidental properties of my original post(s) have come under close scrutiny when people start looking for patterns.

With the awareness of being "hunted", it's surprising how quickly one becomes more cautious about many actions. Of course, I've violated the cardinal rule of my account and used this token more than once, but part of the theory we're testing is that despite using a onetime token (to hyphenate or not, that is the question), my identitiy could still be revealed.

I feel a bit like why the lucky stiff, although his persona had merit, whereas mine is accidental. Coming next week: onetimetoken t-shirts. ;)

I'm a 16 year old soft computation programmer from La Martiniere for Boys, Kolkata, with a passion for Computer Science- particularly artificial intelligence.

I love taking risks in life to accomplish the things that matter most to me. This lead me to take a year off from school last year, to work on a research project, which revolutionizes the field of artificial intelligence.

While my awards and accolades dont define me, they validate my passion for scientific research and innovation:

Last year I worked on algorithm tweaking dynamic frameworks for cancer diagnosis software under the project name "Novel Approach to Detection and Quantification of Malignant Biopsy Tissues by Image Analysis". I went on to represent Team India at ISEF(International Science and Engineering Fair) 2012, and also won the Fourth Grand Award in Computer Science at ISEF.

This year, my project on Reverse Data Synthesis as a revolution in Artificial Intelligence, has once again lead me to represent Team India at ISEF(International Science and Engineering Fair) 2013 held from May 12-17. The project was also among the top 90 projects for the Google Science Fair 2013.

A month back, I decided I would make use of my experience in the field of research, and hop onto entrepreneurship, which has been a dream all through. Currently, Im working on a start up at iAccelerator.
